From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: server: env-gated IOCP completion-port tracing (VSTPOC_ASYNC_TRACE)

Diagnostic-only, OFF unless VSTPOC_ASYNC_TRACE=1 is set in the wineserver
environment. Traces the I/O-completion path that backs Chromium/Mojo sync
IPC so a lost wake-up is visible: async HANDOFF / PACKET / SKIPPED in
server/async.c and completion-queue ADD / POP / GET / SAT in
server/completion.c (the latter naming the waiting thread id). This is what
localised the IK Product Manager "spinner" to a lost condition-variable wake
(fixed in ntdll patch 0015) — kept in-tree, gated, for future lost-wake
hunts. Zero cost when the env var is unset (one getenv, cached).
diff --git a/server/async.c b/server/async.c
index d7f665ba10b..ef008aec53a 100644
--- a/server/async.c
+++ b/server/async.c
@@ -33,6 +33,8 @@
 #include "process.h"
 #include "handle.h"
 
+int vstpoc_async_trace(void);   /* vstpoc: defined below, also used by completion.c */
+
 struct async_cancel
